Hello –

We wanted to let you know that we’ve made some updates to Link’s Terms of Service (https://link.com/terms/preview) and Privacy Policy (https://link.com/privacy/preview). These updates will go into effect on January 16, 2025.

What’s changed?

- Terms of Service (https://link.com/terms). We’ve updated our terms to explain how Link’s beta features work, how we may identify your Link account to help you log in faster at checkout, and to clarify what information is saved to your account.

- Privacy Policy (https://link.com/privacy). We’ve clarified how we collect, use, and share your data, including how we market our services to you.

Why am I receiving this email?

You’re receiving this email because you have an account with Link. Link (https://link.com/) is a safe way to pay faster online. Once you save your payment information at checkout, you’ll be able to quickly autofill your saved payment methods, contact information, and shipping addresses everywhere Link is accepted.

If you have questions about Link, please visit Link support (https://support.link.com/questions/what-is-link).

